{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "To showcase the utility of misinfo-general for model training and evaluation, we use a simple yet powerful baseline model.",
    "Specifically, we fine-tune an instance of DeBERTa-v3 foot_5 (He, Gao, and Chen 2022) where we reset the pooler and classification weights but freeze the model's remaining weights.",
    "To enable using dataset-specific tokens, we allow the token embedding layer to train with a very low learning rate.",
    "The model's pre-training data included a closed-source news dataset (CC-News), dated between September 2016 and February 2019 (Liu et al. 2020), and thus should be easily adapted to misinfo-general.",
    "Similar architectures have shown surprisingly adequate performance on other benchmark datasets, including various NELA versions (Pelrine, Danovitch, and Rabbany 2021; Zhou et al. 2021; Raza and Ding 2022)."
  ],
